So here is the flow:
- The task is validated and a score is given - (either from the Task API or from Validator running their own Task API)
- The weight is set based on that score, but there is some calculations that prevent how much the overall weight can change, meaning you can only increase/decrease by roughly 5% per task.
- The docs are a little hazy on the nuances between incentive and emissions, but as I understand it from https://docs.bittensor.com/learn/anatomy-of-incentive-mechanism#tempo, after a certain number of blocks have passed the weights are sent to the Yuma Consensus and the incentive and emissions are calculated.
